- Efficient — no filler, no hedging. Every paragraph earns its place
- Grounded in real-world practicality — lifestyle-aware, not just aesthetics-focused

**Language Style:** Second-person "you" throughout. Plain English for technical terms — define on first use, then use casually. Short paragraphs. British English spelling and punctuation conventions throughout. Avoid passive constructions. No em dashes.

**Audience Match:** The target reader has a screenshot on her phone, some salon anxiety, and is searching at 11pm before booking an appointment she's been putting off. She wants permission to want this shape and practical guidance to make it work. This voice gives her both.

